<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="KR5c0124-en-8a662c03" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>列子(漢英對照本)</title><editor role="translator">Liang Xiaopeng 梁曉鵬</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><ab>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</ab><availability status="4">The copyright status of this work is unclear</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>列子(漢英對照本)</title>Beijing: Zhonghuashuju, 2005</bibl><ab>Translation of <bibl corresp="#KR5c0124"><title xml:lang="och">列子</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</ab></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2024-01-26T23:57:02.563+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="KR5c0124-start"><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:34:28.672+09:00">Liezi said,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-12T08:54:58.133+09:00">"He who understands the true meaning need not talk,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-12T10:21:06.211+09:00">neither need he who knows all.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:43:57.531+09:00">Speech without words is a kind of speech;</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:44:17.081+09:00">knowledge shown by ignorance is a type of knowledge.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:44:39.492+09:00">Wordlessness as nonspeech</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:45:13.327+09:00">and ignorance as non-knowledge</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-12T08:55:19.002+09:00">are speech and knowledge, too.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:46:11.719+09:00">Therefore, there is nothing unspeakable</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:46:18.943+09:00">or unknowable,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-12T10:56:55.559+09:00">and there is nothing to be talked</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:46:58.932+09:00">or known.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-5a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T09:47:10.134+09:00">That is all,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_004-6a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-12T08:55:38.44+09:00">so what is there to be frightened of?"”</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:01:55.104+09:00">Master Liezi laughed over this and said,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:42:22.686+09:00">"It is absurd either to say that Heaven and Earth will collapse</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.64" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:02:41.929+09:00">or to think that they will not,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.65" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:03:16.19+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.66" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:02:09.954+09:00">for that is beyond our knowledge.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.67" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:03:38.013+09:00">There are both possibilities;</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.70" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:42:11.471+09:00">therefore, it is not possible either to foretell what death is like when one is living</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.71" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:02:14.968+09:00">or to know what life used to be after one's death,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.72" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:02:24.863+09:00">nor is it likely for us either to tell about past in the future</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.73" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:05:16.38+09:00">or to tell about future in the past.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:02:25.362+09:00">In that case, why should we bother worrying about the destiny of Heaven and Earth?"</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_001-12a.74" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:06:28.366+09:00">...the destiny of Heaven and Earth...</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:16:44.822+09:00">He who is wise and intelligent, 如果智谋少的人</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:16:59.938+09:00">when asked to measureprofit and loss, 不估量利害、</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:17:14.631+09:00">to decide falsehood or truth, 不料算虚实、</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:17:26.116+09:00">and to speculateabout human feelings, 不忖度人情，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:17:45.372+09:00">gains one half 所得一半，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:17:53.521+09:00">and loses the other. 所失也一半。</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:18:08.704+09:00">What is thedifference if you measure, 估量和不估量，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:18:18.826+09:00">decide , 料算和不料算，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:18:27.099+09:00">and speculate, 忖度和不忖度，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:18:37.311+09:00">or otherwise? 有什么两样呢？</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:20:01.247+09:00">Onlywhen there is nothing  只有无所估量、</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:20:12.875+09:00">or everything to evaluate无所不估量，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:20:21.56+09:00">can you preserve yourselfagainst loss. 那么就能保全而不丧失。</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:21:07.951+09:00">Ignorance of preservation or loss 不知道保全，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:21:25.57+09:00">will result in thepreservation, disappearance and loss of oneself.也不知道丧失，</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:11:16.808+09:00">这样就能自己保全、</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:11:21.589+09:00">自己消失、</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_006-10a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:12:52.646+09:00">自己丧失。</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:32:45.428+09:00">"Any attempt that catches the opportunity will be fruitful,"said Shi,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:32:53.585+09:00">"and any attempt that misses the opportunity will fail.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:00:40.79+09:00">Your sons have similar interests as ours,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:00:42.692+09:00">and they are right in what they have done, but their effect has been different</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:00:45.282+09:00">because they have missed the right opportunities.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:34:28.191+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T13:59:36.064+09:00">In this world, no principle is always right</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:34:52.159+09:00">and nothing is always wrong.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:35:05.094+09:00">What was used in the past</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:35:09.71+09:00">mighthave to be discarded now ;</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:35:18.647+09:00">what is being abandoned now</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-09T13:35:55.552+09:00">may be adopted again in the time to come.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:00:03.804+09:00">Use or disuse is not right or wrong at all times.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-6a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:09:44.431+09:00">And it is a problem of intelligence to seize the opportunity and to change with the times.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:25:47.448+09:00">"You left him," his friends said, "because you didnot think he understood you ,</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:25:59.26+09:00">but now you are going to die for him.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:26:13.437+09:00">lsn't it the same whether he understands you or not?"</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:27:00.205+09:00">"You arewrong ," replied Zhulishu.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:27:10.482+09:00">"I left because I believed that he did notunderstand me.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:27:29.499+09:00">Now I am going to die for him.</seg><seg corresp="#KR5c0124_tls_008-21a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-10T14:28:03.417+09:00">This proves that he reallydid not understand me.</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>